Gauteng Premier's spokesperson Vuyo Mhaga speaks to #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Almost R6.9bn will be refunded to Gauteng motorists who have been paying their e-toll bills. However, Premier Panyaza Lesufi is unsure how the refunds will be made. WATCH | End of the road for e-tolls He's hoping to finalise the matter before his maiden State of the Province Address later this month. Gauteng Premier's spokesperson Vuyo Mhaga speaks to eNCA in the video above.